'''Larry Hama''' (born [[June 7]], [[1940s|1949]]) is a comic book creator who worked on a few issues in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] comic series.

Hama began working in comics in the mid 1970s at [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC Comics]], but would soon work for [[Marvel Comics]] on the title [[Wikipedia:John Carter, Warlord of Mars|''John Carter, Warlord of Mars'']]. He would gain fame in the early 1980s writing the licensed series based on the [[Wikipedia:G.I. Joe|G.I. Joe]] [[Wikipedia:Hasbro|Hasbro]] toys and he was also credited with the character development for the cartoon series of the same name. Later he would write the hard-hitting war series called [[Wikipedia:The 'Nam|''The 'Nam'']] as well as the [[Wikipedia:Wolverine (comics)|''Wolverine'']] comic series starring the popular Marvel character.

Hama has also appeared in an episode of the television series [[Wikipedia:MASH (television)|''MASH'']] and the sketch comedy show [[Wikipedia:Saturday Night Live|''Saturday Night Live'']].

